  "body": "Related to #8251 \r\n\r\n## Description\r\nDuring Tribute-to-Talk setup, two IPFS-related steps occur:\r\n1. JSON manifest containing TtT settings is uploaded to IPFS via HTTP gateway.\r\n2. It is afterwards automatically fetched to verify request success (using the same gateway URI).\r\n\r\nIn some cases, 1) succeeds, but 2) fails due to a timeout. However, it is often possible to fetch the manifest using an alternative gateway URI.\r\n\r\n## How to reproduce\r\nTry to set up TtT. After confirming the transaction, wait until either the TtT is set properly (steps 1 and 2 succeed), or \r\nin case when step 2 fails, you will see the default TtT message in profile, as if no TtT setup was done:\r\n![Simulator Screen Shot - iPhone X - 2019-05-22 at 13 12 27](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1019573/58166842-5a633a80-7c93-11e9-8a42-bce65f1cc621.png)",
